The opening of the Milan bourse and Italy'snine other stock exchanges has been delayed one hour to 1000GMT by stock market regulatory agency Consob.    A Consob spokesman told Reuters the action was taken "togive operators time to reflect on the agreement betweenTreasury Secretary James Baker and West German officials on theLouvre accord." He did not elaborate.    The Milan Stock Index (MIB), base January 2 equals 1000,closed down 6.26 pct yesterday. REUTER&#3;